1
00:00:00,173 --> 00:00:03,246
Here, they hold prisoners for about

2
00:00:03,940 --> 00:00:05,940
15 days, or 20 days

3
00:00:06,541 --> 00:00:08,341
Then they pay the fines and leave

4
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:12,144
This is the hall we’re entering now. We were detained in it

5
00:00:13,513 --> 00:00:17,765
This hall we’re entering was a prison, and we were detained in it

6
00:00:19,718 --> 00:00:20,871
This is the hall

7
00:00:22,146 --> 00:00:26,705
These windows. They used to put wooden boards over the windows

8
00:00:27,545 --> 00:00:31,199
So the window couldn’t be opened, and so we
wouldn’t see anyone or be seen, and escape

9
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:34,554
All these windows were closed and welded

10
00:00:36,538 --> 00:00:37,658
This is the hall

11
00:00:40,084 --> 00:00:42,489
This prison has four halls

12
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:48,232
This is the first hall, this is the second hall, and the third and the fourth

13
00:00:49,304 --> 00:00:50,487
And there were toilets

14
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:56,786
They brought us food; in the morning it was cheese and <i>samoon</i> [bread roll]

15
00:00:57,789 --> 00:01:02,346
And at noon, a plate of lentils and a bit of rice

16
00:01:05,751 --> 00:01:09,136
This is the second hall, the second hall prison

17
00:01:10,443 --> 00:01:15,493
And this is the third hall of the prison

18
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:19,484
The third hall, of course it had doors

19
00:01:20,225 --> 00:01:24,474
When it became afternoon, they would close this door on us

20
00:01:25,236 --> 00:01:27,489
They locked it on us, and we stayed held here

21
00:01:28,516 --> 00:01:34,230
After the afternoon, no escorts or guards stayed with us

22
00:01:35,889 --> 00:01:37,332
And this is the fourth hall

23
00:01:40,014 --> 00:01:41,018
The fourth hall

24
00:01:42,681 --> 00:01:47,481
And there in the first hall, there is a metal bar hanging from the ceiling

25
00:01:48,325 --> 00:01:51,010
This was for anyone who looked out the window, or disobeyed them

26
00:01:51,057 --> 00:01:53,790
Or anyone who did not follow their orders, they would suspend him from the ceiling

27
00:01:54,214 --> 00:01:59,079
For anyone they wanted to take confessions from, they would hang him from behind

28
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:01,232
A metal bar like this

29
00:02:01,707 --> 00:02:07,149
Up in the ceiling, they used it for torture

30
00:02:08,082 --> 00:02:11,409
They tortured people, they would drop a rope from here

31
00:02:12,322 --> 00:02:14,872
They tied him from behind, like this

32
00:02:15,179 --> 00:02:17,520
Like this, the hands would be behind the back

33
00:02:17,861 --> 00:02:21,317
Then they would pull him up and he would stay hanging until he confessed

34
00:02:21,524 --> 00:02:25,555
And they kept the detained people here to tell them, This is the torture

35
00:02:25,615 --> 00:02:28,917
If you do not confess how much you sold cigarettes for

36
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:32,817
Why did you trim your beard, who taught you?

37
00:02:32,897 --> 00:02:36,799
And do you have contacts with anyone outside the country?

38
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:40,935
And they did not mean outside the country, but outside the caliphate

39
00:02:41,954 --> 00:02:45,852
Or outside the land of the caliphate, who were you talking with?

40
00:02:46,072 --> 00:02:49,543
These were the confessions; they extracted them from people by force

41
00:02:51,423 --> 00:02:55,575
These stairs here lead to the second door

42
00:02:56,607 --> 00:03:00,840
To the church, the church’s second door, and it is connected to the prison

43
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,447
These are the facilities and the toilets

44
00:03:05,127 --> 00:03:08,692
And be aware they did not allow anyone to bathe

45
00:03:10,193 --> 00:03:15,391
And if they were saw someone who did not
pray, they would ask him, Why didn’t you pray?

46
00:03:15,806 --> 00:03:17,953
He would say, I am <i>junub</i> [ritually impure],
And they would say, Why didn’t you wash?

47
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:20,065
He would say to them, There is no hot water. And the weather was cold then

48
00:03:20,485 --> 00:03:21,757
They told him, Wash with cold water

49
00:03:22,524 --> 00:03:23,777
That is how ISIS were

50
00:03:25,010 --> 00:03:26,068
This was their prison

51
00:03:28,321 --> 00:03:31,028
And there was a screen hung in this spot

52
00:03:32,068 --> 00:03:34,436
Where they used to screen their ISIS videos

53
00:03:34,894 --> 00:03:39,761
This is what remains of it, and here is the power socket

54
00:03:40,968 --> 00:03:46,073
They would show horrifying films of beheading and killing

55
00:03:46,295 --> 00:03:50,990
And explosions, IEDs, and car bombs, all shown on the screen

56
00:03:51,411 --> 00:03:54,030
And we were here, and they forced us to watch them

57
00:03:58,148 --> 00:03:59,406
This is the first hall

58
00:04:00,853 --> 00:04:05,905
And next time, we will go to the <i>Thaqila</i> [heavy crimes] Prison

59
00:04:06,393 --> 00:04:09,672
I was also detained there; they call it the <i>Thaqila</i> Prison

60
00:04:11,977 --> 00:04:17,510
It is currently in the Meydan area, the <i>Thaqila</i> Prison is currently in the Meydan area

61
00:04:33,468 --> 00:04:35,148
This is the prison from the outside

62
00:04:35,998 --> 00:04:38,617
These are the windows from the outside and from the inside

63
00:04:38,848 --> 00:04:42,365
They weld the openings so the prisoner will not try to escape

64
00:04:42,755 --> 00:04:44,625
Escape from the prison

65
00:04:46,462 --> 00:04:48,556
They put up sheets of metal and weld them here

66
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:53,908
They call this the <i>Hisba</i> [morality police] base prison in Souq al-Shaarin

67
00:04:55,155 --> 00:04:57,334
In a Christian church

68
00:04:58,407 --> 00:05:02,401
They used churches as prisons and for torture

69
00:05:03,148 --> 00:05:04,448
And halls for lectures

70
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:07,460
There was a hall here, a large hall

71
00:05:08,321 --> 00:05:11,021
They gave lectures there to violators
